text:
We stayed at the hotel for 3 nights during our trip to New York. Having read the reviews, we were very excited for our few days at ModernHaus Soho. The hotel itself is beautifully designed, our bedroom was perfect (queen modern room) with an amazing view of the city and the Le Labo soaps were a great addition! Overall it was great stay, although I would point out a few things - it is a party hotel (we were woken up one our last night by guests smoking weed, and the smell filling out our room. Not something we had planned for/ wanted given the price of the hotel per night); 
the rooftop bar/ pool is run by separate management to the hotel - it closes early to hotel guests and then reopens to the public. I would advise checking on the times before your stay to avoid any let downs or surprises; 
Another point to mention is the cafe/ restaurant, Jumpin Jacks. We had breakfast included, which had very limited options and there seemed to be a disconnect with hotel staff and the Jumpin Jacks staff as to what was included.

The rooftop also turns very much into a club at night, so avoid having a room near the top floor, which other reviews also point out. Our room was on floor 15 and I brought this up at check-in, but  we were assured that we would not be affected by the rooftop noise, however on our last night, the music was unbearably loud at 1-2am. Thankfully the night team were very accommodating and moved us to a lower level (floor 7), where we couldn’t hear the music or noise at all. As we were moving rooms  (after 1am) a group of drunk people were sat by the elevators on our floor making lots of noise too. Also, before relocating to the 7th floor, The night team kindly offered a room on the 5th floor to begin with, which wasn’t impacted by the rooftop music etc, but the next door room was blasting their own music (at around 1am or so), so they gave us the room on the 7th floor. 
 Again a reflection of this hotel being very much a place for those who want to party. 
Despite all of this, the hotel staff were extremely empathetic and dealt with this professionally and without any issues. A big shout out to Gisella and Sheffi for all their help and understanding. They really turned our trip back around and couldn’t be more appreciative to them. So thank you!
